<h2><a name= "b2"></a>SELinux</h2>
<pre>
<CENTER><h2 style="text-align:center;">What is Security Enhanced Linux (SELinux)</h2></CENTER>

SELinux is an additional layer of system security. SELinux is to protect user data with respactive of parent process.
It is provide MAC basied security.It is devlop by NCSA. It is depend only on two policies-
A- Costom Policy
B- Default Policy

<CENTER><h2 style="text-align:center;">How many types of selinux mode(SELinux)</h2></CENTER>
There are three types of selinux mode
A- Enforcing Mode (1)
B- Permissive Mode (0)
C- Disabled Mode
<CENTER><h2 style="text-align:center;">How to set selinux mode</h2></CENTER>

rpm -qa selinux*                -used to check updates all selinux packages
getenforce                      -used to show current selinux mode
setenforce 0                    -used to change permissive mode
setenforce Enforcing (1)        -used to change Enforcing mode
vim /etc/selinux/config         -used to edit {SELINUX = enforsing} default selinux mode settings then reboot system
