<CENTER><h2 style="text-align:center;">What is teamming or bonding</h2></CENTER>

Network teaming is a method for linking network-interface-card (NIC) together logically. Ethernet Channel Bonding enables 
two or more Network Interfaces Card(NIC) to a single virtual NIC card which may increase the bandwidth and provides 
redundancy of NIC Cards. There are five types of teamming
Roundrobin          -This is the default that we are using, it simply sends packets to all interfaces in the team in a 
                     round robin manner, that is one at a time followed by the next interface.
Broadcast	          -All traffic is sent over all ports.
Activebackup	      -One interface is in use while the other is set aside as a backup
Loadbalance	        -Traffic is balanced over all interfaces based on Tx traffic, equal load should be shared over available
                     interfaces.
lacp	              -Implements 802.3ad LACP protocol
<CENTER><h2 style="text-align:center;">How to create activebackup teamming network on NIC </h2></CENTER>

nmcli dev status 
nmcli con add type team con-name team1 ifname team1 config '{"runner": {"name": "activebackup"}}'
nmcli con add type team-slave con-name team-slave1 ifname eth1 master  team1
nmcli con add type team-slave con-name team-slave2 ifname eth2 master  team1
nmcli con show
nmcli con mod team1 ipv4.addresses ipaddress ipv4.method manual
systemctl restart network
teamdctl team1 state 
ping -I team1 ipaddress
